HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1521
By Barrett
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Jonathan Trevor Daniel
of Charlotte.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the untimely passing of Jonathan Trevor Daniel of Charlotte; and
WHEREAS, Jonathan Daniel was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Daniel devoted thirty years to his career in law enforcement, twenty-six
of which were with the Dickson County Sheriff's Office, where he had served with distinction and
unwavering dedication since 2000; throughout the course of his tenure, he held numerous
leadership positions, including patrol deputy, field training officer, detective, SWAT team
member, and K-9 handler, before rising to captain of the criminal investigations division and
terrorism liaison officer, a testament to his skill, integrity, and commitment to public safety and
criminal justice; and
WHEREAS, a gentleman of many talents and interests, Mr. Daniel was an avid
outdoorsman and gun collector and took great joy in sharing his passion and knowledge with his
sons; one of his favorite pastimes was digging up quartz crystals in the Ouachita mountains of
Arkansas, a trip he and his family looked forward to each year; and
WHEREAS, Jonathan Daniel was devoted to his family and always endeavored to
remain true to family values of the highest order; he was most proud of his roles as a husband,
father, and grandfather; and
WHEREAS, left to cherish his memory are his beloved wife of thirty-one years, Kristen
"Kristi" Matlock Daniel; children, Whitney Danielle Barnes, Granville Luke (Kaci) Daniel, and
HJR1521
018333
- 1 -

Hadley Remington Daniel; father, Robert Daniel, Jr.; brother, Troy Daniel; grandchildren, Mason
Harris, Eli Harris, Jett Daniel, Swayze Daniel, Landri Daniel, and Fitz Daniel; stepfather, Gerald
Cunningham; stepbrother, Trent Cunningham; maternal grandmother, May Lankford; and father-
and mother-in-law, Dennis and Brenda Matlock; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Daniel was preceded in death by his mother, Deborah Ann Lankford
Cunningham; his maternal grandfather, William E. Lankford; and his paternal grandparents,
Robert James Daniel and Ruth Mash Daniel Brown; and
WHEREAS, Jonathan Daniel was a jovial and faithful soul who greatly impacted the lives
of those who were blessed to know him, and he leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity
and probity in public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in
all his chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
remember the bountiful life of this exceptional public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Jonathan Trevor Daniel, reflecting fondly upon his
impeccable character and his stalwart commitment to living the examined life with courage and
conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family and friends of Mr. Daniel.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
